c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Claude and Frase share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Short Form, Api Access, Team Collaboration. Where Claude pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Tone Control and Multilingual, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Frase uniquely offers Seo Tools and Templates, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Claude holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Frase scores 7/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Claude offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Frase's starting price of $15/mo. Claude has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Frase does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
