10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Claude is best suited for long form articles, analysis, technical writing, research, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Frase, meanwhile, shines for SEO content, content briefs, SERP analysis, content optimization, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Claude describes itself as \"Anthropic's AI assistant known for nuanced, long-form writing.\" Frase, established in 2016, positions itself as \"AI-powered SEO content optimization and research tool.\" With 7 years between them, Frase brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Claude offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Claude** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Frase is a poor choice — far from it. Frase excels in its own right, particularly for SEO content and content briefs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value exceptional at long-form and nuanced writing, go with Claude. If excellent serp analysis and content brief generation matters more to you, Frase is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
